<subSubSection id="6DB42795FFD3FFA4FF36FA5F38DFFA42" box="[189,966,1429,1456]" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="2511741EFFD3FFA4FF36FA5F38DFFA42" blockId="5.[136,1452,1429,2068]" box="[189,966,1429,1456]" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis id="17DAA80CFFD3FFA4FF36FA5F3A20FA42" bold="true" box="[189,313,1429,1455]" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">Phenology</emphasis>
:—Flowering in May and fruiting from July to November.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6DB42795FFD3FFA4FF36FA733A0FF8FA" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="2511741EFFD3FFA4FF36FA733A0FF8FA" blockId="5.[136,1452,1429,2068]" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis id="17DAA80CFFD3FFA4FF36FA733AFDFA3E" bold="true" box="[189,484,1465,1491]" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">Distribution and ecology</emphasis>
:—The species is known only from Napo, northwestern 
<collectingRegion id="E76ABAFCFFD3FFA4FBD0FA733FA7FA3E" box="[1115,1214,1465,1491]" country="China" name="Guangxi" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">Guangxi</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5DB9348EFFD3FFA4FB42FA733E09FA3E" box="[1225,1296,1465,1491]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">China</collectingCountry>
. And it grows in wet but sunny limestone valleys. Only one small populations with 23 individuals (including only 19 mature trees) have been found in Napo. All mature trees are more than 
<quantity id="E256D9FBFFD3FFA4FC8FF9CB3825F9F1" box="[772,828,1537,1564]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" unit="m" value="15.0">15 m</quantity>
in height and less than 
<quantity id="E256D9FBFFD3FFA4FBCAF9CB3F75F9F1" box="[1089,1132,1537,1564]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" unit="m" value="3.0">3 m</quantity>
is observed for all immature trees. The rarity of this new species may be partially due to human activity because the habitat is also suitable for cultivating cassava, tobacco and other economic plants. And the seeds are often aborted. Comparing to the number of mature trees, the number of immature trees further indicates a decreasing population trend. In addition, all these trees are distributed in a total area of approximately 
<quantity id="E256D9FBFFD3FFA4FD53F95B383EF946" box="[728,807,1681,1707]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" unit="km" value="0.6">0.6 km</quantity>
<superScript id="D2DBD956FFD3FFA4FCACF95B3836F972" attach="left" box="[807,815,1681,1695]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">2</superScript>
. No population was found during repeated field surveys of the surrounding areas. According to the IUCN Categories and Criteria (
<bibRefCitation id="413F09EFFFD3FFA4FC55F97F3F73F922" author="IUCN" box="[990,1130,1717,1743]" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" refId="ref2828" refString="IUCN (2022) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria, Version 15. Available from: https: // www. iucnredlist. org / documents / RedListGuidelines. pdf (accessed 9 February 2022)" type="url" year="2022">IUCN 2022</bibRefCitation>
), the species is classified as Critically Endangered (CR: B1 + 2c). Therefore, it will be necessary to pay close attention to the conservation of this new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6DB42795FFD3FFA4FF36F8EB388BF7F9" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2511741EFFD3FFA4FF36F8EB388BF7F9" blockId="5.[136,1452,1429,2068]" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">
<emphasis id="17DAA80CFFD3FFA4FF36F8EB3AFCF8D6" bold="true" box="[189,485,1825,1851]" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">Taxonomic relationships</emphasis>
:—The comparison with the known species of 
<taxonomicName id="E2AE0F9DFFD3FFA4FB83F8E83F75F8D6" box="[1032,1132,1826,1851]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Reevesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="17DAA80CFFD3FFA4FB83F8E83F75F8D6" box="[1032,1132,1826,1851]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">Reevesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
indicates that 
<taxonomicName id="E2AE0F9DFFD3FFA4FA92F8E83EB2F8D6" authorityName="H. Z. Feng &amp; Y. Feng Huang" authorityYear="2022" box="[1305,1451,1826,1851]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Reevesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="napoensis">
<emphasis id="17DAA80CFFD3FFA4FA92F8E83EB2F8D6" box="[1305,1451,1826,1851]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">R. napoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="E2AE0F9DFFD3FFA4FE9CF88C3991F8B2" authority="Chun (1934: 269" authorityName="Chun" authorityYear="1934" box="[279,648,1861,1887]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Reevesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rotundifolia">
<emphasis id="17DAA80CFFD3FFA4FE9CF88C3AA4F8B2" box="[279,445,1861,1887]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">R. rotundifolia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="413F09EFFFD3FFA4FE4EF88F3991F8B2" author="Chun, W. Y." box="[453,648,1861,1887]" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" refId="ref2623" refString="Chun, W. Y. (1934) Flora of Kwangtung. Sunyatsenia 1: 269 - 230." type="journal volume" year="1934">Chun (1934: 269</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<figureCitation id="BD95689BFFD3FFA4FD1EF88F39C1F88D" box="[661,728,1861,1888]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="6.[136,229,2005,2027]" captionTargetBox="[188,1399,190,1981]" captionTargetId="figure-29@6.[188,1399,190,1981]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 6. Isotype of Reevesia rotundifolia. China, Guangxi, Shangsi (belong to Guangdong before), C. L. Tso 23605(IBSC0004177)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6534770" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6534770/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="E2AE0F9DFFD3FFA4FC91F88C38AFF8B2" authorityName="Tardieu" authorityYear="1945" box="[794,950,1861,1887]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Reevesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orbicularis">
<emphasis id="17DAA80CFFD3FFA4FC91F88C38AFF8B2" box="[794,950,1861,1887]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">R. orbicularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in sharing the characters of the orbicular or ovate-orbicular leaf blade but it has larger phenotypic divergence with 
<taxonomicName id="E2AE0F9DFFD3FFA4FC29F8A03F5EF86E" authorityName="Chun" authorityYear="1934" box="[930,1095,1897,1923]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Reevesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rotundifolia">
<emphasis id="17DAA80CFFD3FFA4FC29F8A03F5EF86E" box="[930,1095,1897,1923]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">R. rotundifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E2AE0F9DFFD3FFA4FBF6F8A03E01F86E" authorityName="Tardieu" authorityYear="1945" box="[1149,1304,1897,1923]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Reevesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orbicularis">
<emphasis id="17DAA80CFFD3FFA4FBF6F8A03E01F86E" box="[1149,1304,1897,1923]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">R. orbicularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation id="682C41A5FFD3FFA4FAACF8A33E62F86E" box="[1319,1403,1897,1923]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="8.[136,224,159,183]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="TABLE 1. Morphological comparison between R. napoensis, R. rotundifolia and R. orbicularis." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/71D12496FFDEFFA9FF03FF553F92FF5A" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" tableUuid="71D12496FFDEFFA9FF03FF553F92FF5A">Table 1</tableCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="E2AE0F9DFFD3FFA4FA18F8A03BE1F84A" authorityName="H. Z. Feng &amp; Y. Feng Huang" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Reevesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="napoensis">
<emphasis id="17DAA80CFFD3FFA4FA18F8A03BE1F84A" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">R. napoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="E2AE0F9DFFD3FFA4FE04F8443932F84A" authorityName="Tardieu" authorityYear="1945" box="[399,555,1933,1959]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Reevesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orbicularis">
<emphasis id="17DAA80CFFD3FFA4FE04F8443932F84A" box="[399,555,1933,1959]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">R. orbicularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the leaf blades upper margin with 3–5 teeth. 
<taxonomicName id="E2AE0F9DFFD3FFA4FBD8F8443FFAF84A" authorityName="H. Z. Feng &amp; Y. Feng Huang" authorityYear="2022" box="[1107,1251,1934,1959]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Reevesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="napoensis">
<emphasis id="17DAA80CFFD3FFA4FBD8F8443FFAF84A" box="[1107,1251,1934,1959]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">R. napoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="E2AE0F9DFFD3FFA4FF03F8783A35F826" authorityName="Chun" authorityYear="1934" box="[136,300,1969,1995]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Reevesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rotundifolia">
<emphasis id="17DAA80CFFD3FFA4FF03F8783A35F826" box="[136,300,1969,1995]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">R. rotundifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the leaf blades upper margin with teeth, but there are very obvious differences. 
<taxonomicName id="E2AE0F9DFFD3FFA4FB46F8783E45F826" authorityName="H. Z. Feng &amp; Y. Feng Huang" authorityYear="2022" box="[1229,1372,1970,1995]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Reevesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="napoensis">
<emphasis id="17DAA80CFFD3FFA4FB46F8783E45F826" box="[1229,1372,1970,1995]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">R. napoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="E2AE0F9DFFD3FFA4FF4DF81C3A7BF802" authorityName="Tardieu" authorityYear="1945" box="[198,354,2005,2031]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Reevesia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="5" pageNumber="202" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="orbicularis">
<emphasis id="17DAA80CFFD3FFA4FF4DF81C3A7BF802" box="[198,354,2005,2031]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">R. orbicularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by cordate base, 7-veined base (vs. truncate or rounded 3-veined, bracts three (vs. one); calyx 4- lobed (vs. 3-lobed) and glabrous petals (vs. puberulent) (
<figureCitation id="BD95689BFFD3FFA4FC88F8333849F7F9" box="[771,848,2041,2068]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1324,1346]" captionTargetBox="[236,1354,196,1289]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[222,1365,190,1300]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. Reevesia napoensis (A-B) flowering branch, (C) top of inflorescence, (D) flower, (E) flowers, (F) flower, a. petal, b. calyx, c. bract. Photographs by Ms. Dong Xin Nong." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6534768" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6534768/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">Figs. 5</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation id="BD95689BFFD3FFA4FCFFF830389DF7F9" box="[884,900,2042,2068]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="7.[136,229,1581,1603]" captionTargetBox="[262,1326,190,1557]" captionTargetId="figure-18@7.[262,1326,190,1557]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 7. Reevesia rotundifolia (A–B) flowering branch, (C–D) flowers, (E) abaxial surface, (F) adaxial surface, (G) fruiting branch, (H) fruit. Photographs by Mr. Bing Liu." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6534772" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6534772/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="202">7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
